claim:
An exploratory moderator analysis examined whether any treatment effects over time on the primary outcome measure varied as a function of initial (Session 1) levels of trust/respect.Results
Recruitment and Participant Characteristics
Of the 886 patients screened by intake coordinators, 494 were referred for potential participation in the study (see CONSORT chart in Figure 1).
title: Figure 1.
caption: CONSORT Diagram Showing Flow of Participants Through Clinical Trial

claim:
Analyses proceeded without incorporating therapist.Comparison of Treatment Conditions on Primary and Secondary Outcomes
On the PROMIS Social Roles and Activities (primary outcome) scale, there were statistically significant effects for time (F = 75.32, DF = 1, 947, p < .0001) and treatment by time interaction (parameter estimate = −.213, 95% CI [−.335, −.091], F = 11.79, DF = 1, 947, p = .0006, d = .22; Figure 2).
title: Figure 2.
caption:
Model-Based PROMIS Scores Over Time
Note. PROMIS = Patient-Reported Outcomes Measurement Information System.
